<font color="#FF0000">AN ARCHIVAL ARMORY BUILE 1893</font><br>
<tt>Wed Jul 30 21:47:44 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
We have in our county Hardin County, Ohio an armory that was built in 1893 and has served many wars and we are desperately trying to save this as a memorial to the servicemen and women.The state of Ohio bought it from the Hardin County commissioners in 1936.It is very unique and it is in the National Archives registered.The money was allocated in 1991 -1992 capitol Improvements budgetof $899,800 for complete renovation.The money never came to ;Hardin County.They moved our servicemen to Lima,Ohio and renovated the Lima Armory.They then purchased an armory up in Medina,Ohio which cost the state $810,000. What the state is saying is since the armory is closed and $385,000 is not enough to renovate it it was to be put on the excess property list and included it in the HB376 disposal list.<br>
They have let it set on a main street with all historical buildings .A building of this stature which to our future generation will be a prized history .The roof is almost gone <br>
the pigeons have taken it over.We know money is tight everywhere but to me this is a part of history the sons and daughters and their sons and daughters of our military men and women should be able to see and touch this fine building.<br>
I feel our legislators only remember us when they need our vote,but by the people and for the people has flown the coop.I feel we have a right to be angry.<br><br>
  
